This topic explains how to install Ops Manager on GCP manually.

## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

You can install Ops Manager on GCP with either the Pivotal Application Service (PAS) or VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid Integrated Edition (TKGI) runtime.

To install Ops Manager on GCP manually, do one of the following:

* Install with PAS. See [Install with PAS](#manual-pas).
* Install with TKGI. See [Install with TKGI](#manual-pks).

## <a id="manual-pas"></a> Install with PAS

To install manually with PAS, do the following:

1. Prepare to deploy Ops Manager. See [Preparing to Deploy Ops Manager on GCP](../gcp/prepare-env-manual.html).

1. Deploy Ops Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on GCP](../gcp/deploy-manual.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on GCP](../gcp/config-manual.html).

1. (Optional). Configure a shared VPC. See [(Optional) Configuring a Shared VPC on GCP](./gcp-shared-vpc.html).

## <a id="manual-pks"></a> Install with TKGI

To install manually with TKGI, do the following:

1. Prepare to deploy Ops Manager. See [Preparing to Deploy Ops Manager on GCP](../gcp/prepare-env-manual.html).

1. Deploy Ops Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on GCP](../gcp/deploy-manual.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on GCP](../gcp/config-manual.html).

1. (Optional). Configure a shared VPC. See [(Optional) Configuring a Shared VPC on GCP](./gcp-shared-vpc.html).

